<br>
The only exception that I ever thought I might allow myself was if during an epic battle I was somehow involved in turning disaster into success. Not something simple like a raid to Splitpaw, but a dragon raid or plane raid. Then, if I managed to turn the tide of battle and save the day I migth take a name to honor the critter. Something like NaggySlayer. But it would only be related to a heroic dead and would not so much be a surname as a mini title.<br>
<br>
Borm <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uwyrdup.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wyrd Up</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/misc_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 488<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/26/02 11:16:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2395.topic&index=24>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> *smiles*</span><hr size=1> Borm and Form... you both should pick up Winterstorm, and roleplay you are brothers!  Or cousins. Or parent/kid, Form would be the gruff older dad, and Borm the kid out to make his way in the world.<br>
